    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.69a-69b_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection
                80 -2</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">69a</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">CHRISTIAN COLLEGE
                        <lb/>
                    COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 19, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>My dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener> 
                <p>A Christian College faculty member doesn't need to tell you how thoroughly our girls enjoyed hearing you read your poetry at our assembly this afternoon. The hush that greeted the reading was assurance enough. If you needed more, you would have had it had you been present in my afternoon English class and heard the enthusiastic comments made by my students. What a rare treat for all of us! And how gracious of you and Mrs. Neihardt to come to us! I am happy that our girls appreciate the privileges they have had.</p>
                
                <p>As we  Missourians say, "Hurry back!"</p>
                
                <p>When you read your first poem, I said to myself, "Of all of Dr Neihardt's poems, that is my favorite!" I found  myself thinking the same thing at the end.
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.69a-69b_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">69b</fw>
                
                    of the second and the third and on an on until finally I couldn't help smiling and had to admit that I love every single <unclear>one equally</unclear>.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mabel A. Buckner</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
